den]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|July 28\n|Philadelphia, Pennsylvania\n|[[Spectrum (arena)|The Spectrum]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|July 30\n|New York City, New York\n|[[Madison Square Garden]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=2wgEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA27&lpg=PA27&dq=stephen+stills+la+forum+1971&source=bl&ots=_l7ryNSYeF&sig=ACfU3U26LdBSWElWFF3__nYACwScSuDehw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjG6OeluIvnAhVSZ8AKHUebBUwQ6AEwE3oECAgQAQ#v=onepage&q=stephen%20stills%20la%20forum%201971&f=false|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=1971-06-12|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref>\n|21,000/<br>21,000<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1971/08/01/archives/stephen-stills-plays-at-garden-in-his-first-solo-concert-here.html|title=Stephen Stills Plays at Garden In His First Solo Concert Here|last=Jahn|first=Mike|date=1971-08-01|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-03-14|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n|Graham Nash Guests\n|-\n|August 1\n|Columbia, Maryland\n|[[Merriweather Post Pavilion|Merriweather Post Pavillion]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 3\n|Louisville, Kentucky\n|[[Indiana Farmers Coliseum|Fairgrounds Coliseum]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 6\n|Oklahoma City, Oklahoma\n|[[Oklahoma State Fair Arena|Fairgrounds Arena]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 7\n|Minneapolis, Minnesota\n|[[Minneapolis Auditorium]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 9\n|Denver, Colorado\n|[[Denver Coliseum]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 10\n|Salt Lake City, Utah\n|[[Salt Palace (arena)|Salt Palace]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 12\n|Oakland, California\n|[[Oracle Arena|Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 14\n|Phoenix, Arizona\n|[[Arizona Veterans Memorial Coliseum]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 15\n|San Diego, California\n|[[San Diego Sports Arena]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 17\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Inglewood, California\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[The Forum (Inglewood, California)|The Forum]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=2wgEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA27&lpg=PA27&dq=stephen+stills+la+forum+1971&source=bl&ots=_l7ryNSYeF&sig=ACfU3U26LdBSWElWFF3__nYACwScSuDehw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjG6OeluIvnAhVSZ8AKHUebBUwQ6AEwE3oECAgQAQ#v=onepage&q=stephen%20stills%20la%20forum%201971&f=false|title=Billboard|last=Inc|first=Nielsen Business Media|date=1971-06-12|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|language=en}}</ref>\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 18\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 20\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Berkeley, California\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Berkeley Community Theatre|Berkeley Community Theater]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|August 21\n|\n|\n|}\n\n===Typical tour set list===\nAll songs written by Stephen Stills, except where noted.\n# \"Rock and Roll Woman\"\n# \"Questions\"\n# \"[[Helplessly Hoping]]\"\n# \"Fishes and Scorpions\"\n# \"Go Back Home\"\n# \"[[Love the One You're With]]\"\n# \"Black Queen\"\n# \"Change Partners\"\n# \"Know You Got to Run\" (Stills, John Hopkins)\n# \"Word Game\"\n# \"Do for the Others\"\n# \"I'd Have to Be Crazy\"  ([[Steven Fromholz]])\n# \"Texas Train Ride\" ([[Steven Fromholz]])\n# \"Jesus Gave Love Away For Free\"\n# \"You Don't Have to Cry\"\n# \"49 Bye-Byes/[[For What It's Worth]]\"\n# \"Ecology Song\"\n# \"Open Secret\"\n# \"Lean On Me Baby\" (Wayne Jackson)\n# \"[[Bluebird (Buffalo Springfield song)|Bluebird Revisited]]\"\n# \"Cherokee\"\n# \"How Long\" \n# \"[[Find the Cost of Freedom]]\"\n\n===Tour personnel===\n*[[Stephen Stills]]{{snd}}vocal, guitar, keyboards\n*[[Steven Fromholz]]{{snd}}guitar, vocals\n*[[Paul Harris (musician)|Paul Harris]]{{snd}}keyboards\n*Calvin \"Fuzzy\" Samuels{{snd}}bass guitar\n*[[Dallas Taylor (drummer)|Dallas Taylor]]{{snd}}drums\n*[[Joe Lala]]{{snd}}percussion\n*[[The Memphis Horns]]{{snd}}horn section ([[Wayne Jackson (musician)|Wayne Jackson]], Roger Hopps, Jack Hale, [[Andrew Love (musician)|Andrew Love]] , Sidney George, [[Floyd Newman]])\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Stephen Stills}}\n\n[[Category:1971 albums]]\n[[Category:Stephen Stills albums]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records albums]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo